@EchoÂñµ‰∏ÉÁà∑: Âç¢Âç°ÊñØ¬∑Â§öËØ≠ÁßçÊñáË±™¬∑‰∏ñÁïåÁ¨¨‰∏ÄÁå™Âêπ¬∑Áå™Ê≥¢Ëøô‰πàÂ§öÂπ¥ÊàëÈÉΩËÆ∞ÁùÄÂë¢¬∑Êàë‰ª¨‰∏§ÂÆ∂ÂæàÁÜü¬∑ÊàëËøòÊòØÂè´ËÄÅÁå™Schweini¬∑Ê≥¢Â§öÂ∞îÊñØÂü∫

And even in far-off Asia one thinks of Basti: Poldi writes him these beautiful lines!

Hi Basti!

I remember when I met you for the first time. You had such blond dyed hair, you were the guy from Bavaria and I was the boy from K√∂lle. We were almost teenagers and just wanted to kick. That was 2004 in the U21 national team. Right in the first game I gave you a goal - with us it went straight.
Then we became national players together and we were the boys under Ballack, Kahn and Co. We fought it through, that welded us together. We did not stick together, but we did a lot together. It was always cool because we never took ourselves too seriously. But now we can also say quite confidently: Back then we were enthusiastic about the German fans again because they simply looked at the joy of football.
We always had a great time together, but the class clowns, as many thought, we were not. We knew when it was serious and then we could rely on each other. In the game and also privately. „ÄêWhen I moved to Munich, you helped me a lot. I will not forget that. Our families know each other well. For me it was very special that I was allowed to attend your wedding a year ago. „ÄëBut now I've said enough about us: Now it's your turn!
This farewell game at Bayern, you deserve it! For me you have a place in the club like the big ones: Beckenbauer, Olli Kahn, Gerd Mueller, Philipp Lahm and what they are called. You Basti, you are one of them!
„ÄêIf you can not be satisfied with your career, who will? You lived your dream in the national team and at your favorite club. You have become a legend! World Champion, Triple Winner, Endurance Champion and what you did not win. You have achieved something extraordinary.„Äë
But it also includes the sad moments. The lost Champions League final in Munich or the World Cup semi-finals. You never gave up and in the end you still won the titles!
But for me, one thing is also very important: When you come to Bayern, you will always be welcomed with open arms, because you next to your performance of your career and I find that so cool in you.
I'm really happy to have you as a friend! Even if you play in Chicago now and I in Japan, we'll always meet each other.

All the best, Schweini, your Poldi!
